{"type":"message","id":"1cc14d55","parentId":"adeedca8","timestamp":"2026-03-03T11:05:03.428Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"This is clearly a bug in the QVeris API. Every tool returns the same error - it says parameters are missing even when they're being provided. \n\nLet me check if maybe the params need to be provided differently - perhaps as a string or in a different format. Or maybe there's an issue with the API key permissions.\n\nActually wait - I wonder if maybe the tool_id format is wrong. Let me try to see if there's a simpler tool that works.\n\nLet me try one more thing - execute a tool without the .X suffix in the tool_id:","thinkingSignature":"30ea38c17edc80570983328eb3ef3e451b5d6a2f6f3bca3c64f1c9d5d78f0c61"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_3aohlo1zvdvu_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s -X POST \"https://qveris.ai/api/v1/search\" \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -H \"Authorization: Bearer $QVERIS_API_KEY\" \\\n  -d '{\"query\": \"trending stock news\", \"limit\": 3}' | jq '.results[].tool_id'","timeout":30}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.5","usage":{"input":27921,"output":218,"cacheRead":13984,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":42123,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772535887469}}
